# Backend Configuration

To connect to the backend (fibo-backend), add these variables to your `.env` file:

```env
# Backend base URL
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://fibo-backend.onrender.com

# Optional: initial token (if you have a saved token)
VITE_AUTH_TOKEN=
```

## FIBO API Configuration (alternative image generation)

If you prefer to use the FIBO API instead of Gemini, configure these variables:

```env
# FIBO API key
VITE_FIBO_API_KEY=your_fibo_api_key_here

# Generation endpoint path (default: /fibo/image/generate)
VITE_FIBO_GENERATE_PATH=/fibo/image/generate

# Authentication header type: authorization | api_token | x-api-key | x-api-token
# (default: api_token)
VITE_FIBO_AUTH_HEADER=api_token
```

## Usage in code

### Generating images/videos
```typescript
import { generationApi } from './services/generationApi';
import { useAuthStore } from './stores';

const token = useAuthStore((state) => state.token);

// Generate image
const response = await generationApi.generateImage({
  prompt: "A futuristic robot",
  lighting: "Studio",
  style: "Cinematic",
  aspectRatio: "16:9"
}, token);
```

### Authentication
```typescript
import { authApi } from './services/authApi';
import { useAuthStore } from './stores';

const { setToken, setUser } = useAuthStore();

// Login
const { token, user } = await authApi.login({
  email: "user@example.com",
  password: "password"
});

setToken(token);
setUser(user);
```

## Available endpoints

### Generation
- `POST /generation/image` - Generate image
- `POST /generation/video` - Generate video
- `GET /generation` - Get history
- `GET /generation/{id}` - Get a specific generation

### Authentication
- `POST /auth/login` - Login
- `POST /auth/register` - Register
- `POST /auth/logout` - Logout
- `POST /auth/validate` - Validate token

### Projects
- `POST /projects` - Save project
- `GET /projects` - Get projects
